<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When converting one measure to another with a precision higher than 2 
the precision doesn't seem to be taken into account and digits after the "." are always zeroed.</p>

<p>$locale = new Zend_Locale('en_US');</p>

<p>$number = new Zend_Measure_Length(12.3456,Zend_Measure_Length::STANDARD,$locale);
$number-&gt;convertTo('CENTIMETER',4);</p>

<p>echo $number-&gt;getValue(4);</p>

<p>returns: 1235.00</p>

<p>changing line 130 in Measure/Abstract.php to:
$value = $this-&gt;getValue(4);
works arround the problem.</p>

    </div>
